Aeroporti di Roma CEO Expected to Resign, Messaggero Says

-- B y   S o n i a   S i r l e t t i
-- 
2011-09-28T06:21:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/aeroporti-di-roma-ceo-expected-to-resign-messaggero-says.html
Aeroporti di Roma SpA Chief
Executive Officer Giulio Maleci will resign tomorrow because of
strategy differences with the Benetton family, daily  Il
Messaggero  said.  Maleci will be replaced on an interim basis by Carlo Bertazzo, the newspaper reported without saying where it
obtained the information. The Benettons control the airport
management company through  Gemina SpA. (GEM)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Sonia Sirletti in Milan at 
 ssirletti@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at 
 fconnelly@bloomberg.net  